          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2014-09-03T16:32:34Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Spurring Teacher Education Movement for STEM Act or the STEM for STEM Act - Expresses the sense of Congress that:</p> <ul> <li>the United States should be at the forefront of science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) education;</li> <li>students in low-income and rural areas have limited access to STEM resources;</li> <li>teachers should have high-quality professional development opportunities in STEM; and</li> <li>teacher professional development should provide strategies for integrating STEM education across all demographics.</li> </ul> <p>Amends the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 to allow local educational agencies to use grant funds under the Rural and Low-Income School program to train teachers to provide STEM education.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2014-06-25T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <actionDate>2014-06-25</actionDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
